Job Description:
This is a part-time and remote job for Principal Machine Learning ( or Artificial Intelligence ) Engineers in Healthcare.
AAFIE Artificial Intelligence Labs at AAFIE focuses on the research and development of digital transformation solutions for manufacturing and healthcare industries. Our founding members include AI professors from UC Berkeley as well as senior engineers from Silicon Valley. Accomplishing our mission requires doing really big things for customers. We are currently looking for innovative, collaborative and curious people who love to solve real-world problems in Healthcare industry using Machine Learning and AI.
Primary Responsibilities:
Lead research and development projects in Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence;
Collaborate with domain experts in Healthcare to identify critical challenges and opportunities for AI-driven improvements, and prioritize projects accordingly;
Develop innovative Machine Learning and/or Deep Learning and/or Reinforcement Learning algorithms for leveraging multiple sources of data to improve the quality of life for patients, predict diseases/risks for seniors, and develop digital medical solutions for healthcare providers;
Evaluate and monitor Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence models to continuously improve the performance of the digital medical systems;
Collaborate with other team members to code, train, test, deploy, and iterate on Artificial Intelligence based systems.
Required Qualifications:
A minimum of MS degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Statistics, or a related field with a focus on Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, or a similar area.
3+ years of research or development experience in Machine Learning and/or Artificial Intelligence;
Experience training and evaluating machine learning and deep learning models (e.g. time-series modeling, tree-based models, ensemble learning, neural networks, reinforcement learning, etc.) and a good understanding of statistical techniques and concepts;
Strong programming skills in Python, R, or other relevant programming languages;
Proficiency in various machine learning frameworks, libraries, and tools, such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras, or scikit-learn;
Experience working with large-scale data sets and distributed computing tools (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, or similar technologies);
MLOps experience is a plus.
